#: Game
msgid "Welcome to **The Ross ℤ Game**. The object of this game is to build number theory\n"
"over ℤ, the integers, from nothing but the Ross axioms.\n"
"\n"
"## What is Lean?\n"
"\n"
"Lean is a proof assistant. As we write proofs, a panel dynamically reports our\n"
"**givens** and our **goals**. As goals get cleared, we stock an inventory of\n"
"rigorous, *machine-verified* theorems that can be used to prove new goals.\n"
"\n"
"This game does **not** import §0. ***We start from scratch.*** We define ℤ\n"
"as an ordered ring satisfying the well-ordering principle, and nothing else.\n"
"\n"
"There is no §1 tactic here. There is Well-Ordering, or there is nothing."
msgstr ""

